250 g Ground Turkey
170 g Green Beans
113 g Mushrooms
113 mL Cream
7 g Thyme
56 g Yellow Onion, chopped
¾ cup Jasmine Rice
7.5 g Chicken Stock Powder
1 unit(s) Sour Cream
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
½ tbsp Oil*

Before starting, wash and dry all produce.
Trim green beans, then halve.
Quarter mushrooms.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high.
When the pan is hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter, turkey, onions and mushrooms. Cook for 4-6 min, breaking up turkey into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.** Season with salt and pepper.

Using a strainer, rinse rice until water runs clear. Add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, rice and thyme sprigs. Season with salt and pepper.
Add cream, stock powder and 1 cup (2 cups) water. Bring to a boil over high.
Reduce heat to medium-low. Cover and cook for 10-12 min, stirring occasionally, until rice is tender and water is absorbed.
Add green beans and 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) water. Cook for 3-4 min, stirring often, until green beans are tender and water is absorbed.

Carefully remove thyme sprigs and discard.
Add sour cream. Stir to combine.
Divide turkey mixture between plates.